 friend. She found joy in the simple things - a good book, a long walk, a starry night - and she shared that joy with those around her. Her laughter was contagious, her spirit indomitable, and her love unconditional.\n\nToday, as we gather to honor Eleanor's life, we are reminded of the profound impact she had on our lives and on the world. Her legacy will live on in the minds of her students, in the pages of her research, and in the stars she so dearly loved.\n\nAs we say our final goodbyes, let us remember Eleanor not just for her scientific achievements, but for her kindness, her wisdom, and her unqu",
